org.apache.flex.compiler.css

Interface ICSSNamespaceDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ICSSNode, ISourceLocation
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CSSNamespaceDefinition

    public interface ICSSNamespaceDefinition
extends ICSSNode
    Namespace definition maps a namespace URI to a prefix name. For example: 
     @namespace s "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/spark";
    The @namespace directive maps "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/spark" to prefix "s". The selector can be gated with "s" to style "spark" components, like s|Button .

    Every CSS document can have a default namespace definition without specifying a prefix. 

     @namespace "library://ns.adobe.com/flex/mx";
    Then all the type selectors without a namespace prefix defaults to components in the default namespace.
